{"title_page": "4th Armored Brigade (People's Republic of China)", "text_new": "{{One source|date=April 2020}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name                     = 4th Tank Division (1967\u201398)<br>4th Armored Division (1998\u20132011)<br>4th Armored Brigade (2011-)\n| image                         = \n| caption                       = \n| nickname                      = \n| motto                         = \n| themesong                     = \n| colors                        = \n| march                         = \n| ceremonial_chief              = \n| type                          = [[armoured warfare|Armored]]\n| status                        = \n| dates                         =  \n| country                       = {{flagicon|China}} China\n| allegiance                    = \n| command_structure             = [[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army]]\n| size                          = Brigade\n| specialization                = \n| challenge                     = \n| response                      = \n| current_commander             = \n| garrison                      = [[Hailong]], [[Jilin]]\n| battles                       =  \n| notable_commanders            = \n| anniversaries                 = \n| identification_symbol         = \n| identification_symbol_label   = \n| identification_symbol_2       = \n| identification_symbol_2_label = \n}}\n\nThe '''4th Tank Division''' ({{zh|\u5766\u514b\u7b2c4\u5e08}}) was formed on 1 April 1969 from 237th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[48th Motorized Infantry Brigade (People's Republic of China)|32nd Army Division]], 252nd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[46th Motorized Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|46th Army Division]], 253rd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[47th Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|47th Army Division]] and 397th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[192nd Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|192nd Army Division]].\n\nAs of 19 August 1969, the division was composed of:\n*13th Tank Regiment (former 237th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*14th Tank Regiment (former 252nd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*15th Tank Regiment (former 253rd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*16th Tank Regiment (former 397th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment).\n\nIn 1972 the division retired all its [[SU-76]]s and equipped with only [[T-34]]s.\n\nIn February 1976, 14th Tank Regiment was detached and became Tank Regiment, 16th Army Corps. 16th Tank Regiment was detached and became Tank Regiment, 68th Army Corps. 1st Independent Tank Regiment of Shenyang Military Region was attached and renamed as new 14th Tank Regiment.\n\nFrom 1980 to 1982 the division re-equipped with 5 battalions of [[Type 59 tank|Type-59]] and [[Type 59 tank|Type-59-1]] medium tanks.\n\nOn 1 January 1 1983 the division was put under command of [[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army Corps]]. Armored Infantry Regiment and Artillery Regiment activated. By then the division was composed of:[[File:4th Tank Division, 16th Army, 1985.png|thumb|400px|4th Tank Division, Organization from 1984 to 1998.]]\n* 13th Tank Regiment\n* 14th Tank Regiment\n* 15th Tank Regiment\n* Armored Infantry Regiment\n* Artillery Regiment\n\nIn 1985 the division is attached to [[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army]]. \n\nIn 1998 the division was renamed '''4th Armored Division''' ({{zh|\u88c5\u7532\u7b2c4\u5e08}}). The Armored Infantry Regiment was disbanded and absorbed into tank regiments which became armored regiments. By then the division was composed of:\n* 13th Armored Regiment\n* 14th Armored Regiment\n* 15th Armored Regiment\n* Artillery Regiment\n\nIn late 2011 the division was split into two: the division itself became '''4th Armored Brigade''' ({{zh|\u88c5\u7532\u7b2c4\u65c5}}), while half of its battalions formed [[204th Mechanized Infantry Brigade (People's Republic of China)|204th Mechanized Infantry Brigade]].\n\n==References==\n*\u88c5\u75324\u5e08\u6cbf\u9769\u53f2\uff0c[http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_693249e20100k4tj.html Chinese-only website]\n\n{{People's Liberation Army Divisions}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:4th Armoured Brigade (People's Republic Of China)}}\n[[Category:Armoured brigades of the People's Liberation Army]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1969]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox military unit\n|unit_name=4th Tank Division (1967\u201398)<br>4th Armored Division (1998\u20132011)<br>4th Armored Brigade (2011-)\n|image=\n|caption=\n|nickname=\n|motto=\n|themesong=\n|colors=\n|march=\n|ceremonial_chief=\n|type=[[armoured warfare|Armored]]\n|status=\n|dates= \n|country={{flagicon|China}} China\n|allegiance=\n|command_structure=[[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army]]\n|size=Brigade\n|specialization=\n|challenge='\n|response=\n|current_commander=\n|garrison=[[Hailong]], [[Jilin]]\n|battles= \n|notable_commanders=\n|anniversaries=\n|identification_symbol=\n|identification_symbol_label=\n|identification_symbol_2=\n|identification_symbol_2_label=\n}}\n\nThe '''4th Tank Division''' ({{zh|\u5766\u514b\u7b2c4\u5e08}}) was formed on April 1, 1969 from 237th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[48th Motorized Infantry Brigade (People's Republic of China)|32nd Army Division]], 252nd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[46th Motorized Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|46th Army Division]], 253rd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[47th Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|47th Army Division]] and 397th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment from [[192nd Infantry Division (People's Republic of China)|192nd Army Division]].\n\nAs of August 19th, 1969, the division was composed of:\n*13th Tank Regiment (former 237th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*14th Tank Regiment (former 252nd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*15th Tank Regiment (former 253rd Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment);\n*16th Tank Regiment (former 397th Tank Self-Propelled Artillery Regiment).\n\nIn 1972 the division retired all its [[SU-76]]s and equipped with only [[T-34]]s.\n\nIn February 1976 14th Tank Regiment was detached and became Tank Regiment, 16th Army Corps. 16th Tank Regiment was detached and became Tank Regiment, 68th Army Corps. 1st Independent Tank Regiment of Shenyang Military Region was attached and renamed as new 14th Tank Regiment.\n\nFrom 1980 to 1982 the division re-equipped with 5 battalions of [[Type 59 tank|Type-59]] and [[Type 59 tank|Type-59-1]] medium tanks.\n\nFrom January 1st, 1983 the division was put under command of [[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army Corps]]. Armored Infantry Regiment and Artillery Regiment activated.\n\nBy then the division was composed of:[[File:4th Tank Division, 16th Army, 1985.png|thumb|400px|4th Tank Division, Organization from 1984 to 1998.]]\n*13th Tank Regiment;\n*14th Tank Regiment;\n*15th Tank Regiment;\n*Armored Infantry Regiment;\n*Artillery Regiment.\n\nFrom 1985 the division is attached to [[16th Army (People's Republic of China)|16th Army]]. \n\nIn 1998 the division was renamed '''4th Armored Division''' ({{zh|\u88c5\u7532\u7b2c4\u5e08}}). The Armored Infantry Regiment was disbanded and absorbed into tank regiments which became armored regiments.\n\nBy then the division was composed of:\n*13th Armored Regiment;\n*14th Armored Regiment;\n*15th Armored Regiment;\n*Artillery Regiment.\n\nIn late 2011 the division was split into two: the division itself became '''4th Armored Brigade''' ({{zh|\u88c5\u7532\u7b2c4\u65c5}}), while half of its battalions formed [[204th Mechanized Infantry Brigade (People's Republic of China)|204th Mechanized Infantry Brigade]].\n\n==References==\n\n*\u88c5\u75324\u5e08\u6cbf\u9769\u53f2\uff0c[http://blog.sina.com.cn/s/blog_693249e20100k4tj.html Chinese-only website]\n\n{{People's Liberation Army Divisions}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:4th Armoured Brigade (People's Republic Of China)}}\n[[Category:Armoured brigades of the People's Liberation Army]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 1969]]\n", "name_user": "ThePersecuted", "label": "safe", "comment": "MOS:DATESNO& single ref source", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/4th_Armored_Brigade_(People%27s_Republic_of_China)"}
{"title_page": "Google Map Maker", "text_new": "{{short description|Collaborative mapping tool}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = Google Map Maker\n| logo             = Google Map Maker Logo.svg\n| logo_size        = 72px\n| screenshot       = Google Map Maker \u00cdsafj\u00f6r\u00f0ur.png\n| caption          = Screenshot of the town of [[\u00cdsafj\u00f6r\u00f0ur]], [[Iceland]], in Google Map Maker\n| collapsible      = yes\n| collapsetext     = Screenshot\n| url              = {{URL|https://www.google.com/mapmaker}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Google Map Maker has closed - Map Maker Help |url=https://support.google.com/mapmaker/answer/7195127 |website=support.google.com |publisher=Google |accessdate=8 September 2019 |date=31 March 3017}}</ref>\n| commercial       =\n| type             = [[Web mapping]]\n| language         = Multilingual\n| registration     = Yes\n| owner            = [[Google]]\n| launch_date      = {{start date and age|2008|6|23}}\n| current_status   = Defunct {{end date and age|2017|3|31}}\n| revenue          =\n}}\n\n'''Google Map Maker''' was a map editing service launched by [[Google]] in June 2008.<ref>{{cite web |title = Making your mark on the world |first1 = Lalitesh |last1 = Katragadda |first2 = Sanjay |last2 = Jain |url = https://maps.googleblog.com/2008/06/making-your-mark-on-world.html |website = Google Maps blog |publisher = [[Google]] |date = 23 June 2008 |accessdate = 16 January 2017 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313173331/https://maps.googleblog.com/2008/06/making-your-mark-on-world.html |archivedate = 13 March 2016}}</ref> In geographies where it is hard to find providers of good map data, user contributions were used to increase map quality. Changes to Google Map Maker were intended to appear on [[Google Maps]] only after sufficient review by Google moderators. Google Map Maker was used at Google [[Mapathon]] events held annually.\n\nIn November 2016, Google announced that Google Map Maker would be retired and merged with Google Maps.<ref name=\"lumb\">{{cite web |title = Google will retire Map Maker, the tool that let anyone update Maps |first = David |last = Lumb |url = https://www.engadget.com/2016/11/09/google-will-retire-map-maker-the-tool-that-let-anyone-update-ma/ |website = [[Engadget]] |date = 9 November 2016 |accessdate = 16 January 2017 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161115035749/https://www.engadget.com/2016/11/09/google-will-retire-map-maker-the-tool-that-let-anyone-update-ma/ |archivedate = 15 November 2016 |url-status = live }}</ref> Google Map Maker was officially shut down on March 31, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Map Maker update [February 2017]|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!topic/map-maker/5m7xLsiEFB0|publisher=Google Product Forums|accessdate=2 March 2017|date=24 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Interface==\nUsing the find or browse tools, contributors were able to add and draw features directly onto a map where the borders had already been drawn, and could add features such as [[road]]s, [[railway]]s, [[river]]s and so on. In addition, users could add specific buildings and services onto the map such as local [[business]]es and services.<ref name=\"lumb\" />\n\nThree kinds of drawing tools were available: placemark (a single point of interest on the map), line (for drawing roads, railways, rivers, and the like) and [[polygon]] (for defining boundaries and borders, adding parks, lakes and other large features). The approach encouraged by users and by Google was to trace features such as roads from the existing satellite imagery. This approach was not useful in areas with poor satellite imagery, and users consequently created less map data in those areas.\n\nNew users' contributions were moderated by more experienced users or reviewers at Google to ensure quality and prevent [[vandalism]]. As users made more successful contributions, their edits were less closely monitored and may have been published on the map straight away. Certain larger features may have taken a long time to appear on the map as they were waiting to be rendered by the server.\n\nContributors could assign areas of the map as their 'neighbourhood', that is an area they know well enough to make detailed contributions to. Users could also moderate the contributions of others within their neighbourhood. This information was private; the neighbourhood a user selected was not publicly associated with the users' account.<ref name=pulse>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/mapmaker/pulse |title=Google Map Maker |publisher=Google.com |date= |accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Availability==\nAs of 6 March 2016, the service was available in [[Bangladesh]], [[Belarus]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Brazil]], [[Cambodia]], [[Canada]], [[Costa Rica]], [[Croatia]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Denmark]] (not including [[Greenland]] and the [[Faroe Islands]]), [[Egypt]], [[El Salvador]], [[Estonia]], [[France]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], [[Germany]], [[Hungary]], [[India]], [[Iran]], [[Iraq]], [[Italy]], [[Kazakhstan]], [[Kuwait]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Malaysia]], [[Mexico]], [[Moldova]], [[Morocco]], [[Nepal]], the [[Netherlands]], [[New Zealand]], [[Nigeria]], [[Pakistan]], [[Panama]], [[Peru]], the [[Philippines]], [[Poland]], [[Puerto Rico]], [[Romania]], [[Russia]], [[Serbia]], [[Slovakia]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Sweden]], [[Taiwan]], [[Ukraine]], the [[United Kingdom]], the [[United States]], [[Venezuela]], and [[Vietnam]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Countries being mapped|url=https://support.google.com/mapmaker/answer/155415?hl=en|website=Map Maker Help|accessdate=24 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==2015 vandalism incident==\nIn April 2015, Google removed user-created Map Maker content that showed an \"[[Android (operating system)|Android]] robot urinating on the [[Apple Inc.#Logo|Apple logo]]\" and a separate feature saying \"Google review policy is crap\", after they were discovered on [[Google Maps]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hern|first1=Alex|title=Google Maps hides an image of the Android robot urinating on Apple|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/apr/24/google-maps-hides-an-image-of-the-android-robot-pissing-on-apple|accessdate=10 May 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=24 April 2015}}</ref> Following the \"large scale prank\", Google disabled auto-approval and user moderation, and on 8 May, the Map Maker team announced that editing would be temporarily disabled worldwide as of 12 May 2015.<ref name=\"BBC News 12 May 2015\">{{cite web | title= Google suspends Map Maker because of vandalism|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-32704566 |date= 12 May 2015 | website= BBC News | accessdate= 12 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kanakarajan|first1=Pavithra|title=Map Maker will be temporarily unavailable for editing starting May 12, 2015|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!category-topic/map-maker/news-and-announcements/crFEbGXJ-HI|accessdate=10 May 2015|publisher=Google Product Forums|date=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nGoogle reenabled the service in six countries in August 2015, with plans to enable in other countries in the following weeks.<ref name=\"6country\">{{cite web|last1=Kanakarajan|first1=Pavithra|title=Map Maker will be enabled in six countries starting today|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!topic/map-maker/JeAFzDcTFfQ|website=Google Product Forums|publisher=Alphabet Inc.|accessdate=16 August 2015}}</ref> On 10 August, editing was re-opened to Bangladesh, Brazil, Canada, India, the Philippines, and Ukraine; Google relied on regional moderators to review edits as an extra precaution, in addition to automated and human moderation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://searchengineland.com/google-map-maker-back-up-in-six-countries-more-to-follow-227473 |title=Google Map Maker Back Up In Six Countries With More To Follow Soon |last=Sterling |first=Greg |work=[[Search Engine Land]] |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref> On 26 August, Google Map Maker re-opened to 45 more countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2490133,00.asp |title=Google Map Maker Back in Action in U.S. |author=Moscaritolo, Angela |work=[[PC Magazine]] |date=August 26, 2015 |accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism==\nMap Maker required contributors to grant Google a \"... perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free, and non-exclusive license to reproduce, adapt, modify, translate, publish, publicly perform, publicly display, distribute, and create derivative works of the User Submission\".<ref>[http://www.google.com/mapmaker/mapfiles/s/terms_mapmaker.html Terms of Service for Google Map Maker]</ref> While Google provided a form to request Map Maker data downloads,<ref>{{cite web|title=Map Maker Data Download|url=https://services.google.com/fb/forms/mapmakerdatadownload/|publisher=Google|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> it provided no programmatic access to data. There were expressions of concern that Google was taking advantage of open communities,<ref>{{cite web|last=Maron|first=Mikel|title=We Need to Stop Google's Exploitation of Open Communities |url=http://brainoff.com/weblog/2011/04/11/1635|publisher=Brainoff|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> and large contributors to Map Maker, such as the [[World Bank]]'s project partnering with Google, were viewed critically.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fitzpatrick|first=Alex|title=Google Maps & World Bank Join Forces, So Why Isn\u2019t Everyone Smiling?|url=http://mashable.com/2012/01/19/google-maps-world-bank/|publisher=Mashable|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Heller|first=Nathaniel|title=Why We're Worried about Google's Deal with the World Bank |url=http://www.globalintegrity.org/blog/google-world-bank-map-deal|publisher=Global Integrity|accessdate=23 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Yandex Map Editor]]\n* [[Mapping Bangladesh]]\n* [[Here Map Creator]]\n* [[OpenStreetMap]]\n* [[Wikimapia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://mapmaker.google.com/mapmaker Google Map Maker website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/sites.google.com/site/mapmakerpedia/ Google Map Makerpedia]\n\n{{Google Maps navbox}}\n{{Google Inc.}}\n{{OpenStreetMap}}\n\n[[Category:Crowdsourcing]]\n[[Category:Google Maps|Maker]]\n[[Category:Google services|Map Maker]]\n[[Category:Web Map Services]]\n[[Category:2008 software]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Internet properties disestablished in 2017]]\n[[Category:Discontinued Google software|Map Maker]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Collaborative mapping tool}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = Google Map Maker\n| logo             = Google Map Maker Logo.svg\n| logo_size        = 72px\n| screenshot       = Google Map Maker \u00cdsafj\u00f6r\u00f0ur.png\n| caption          = Screenshot of the town of [[\u00cdsafj\u00f6r\u00f0ur]], [[Iceland]], in Google Map Maker\n| collapsible      = yes\n| collapsetext     = Screenshot\n| url              = {{URL|https://www.google.com/mapmaker}}<ref>{{cite web |title=Google Map Maker has closed - Map Maker Help |url=https://support.google.com/mapmaker/answer/7195127 |website=support.google.com |publisher=Google |accessdate=8 September 2019 |date=31 March 2017}}</ref>\n| commercial       =\n| type             = [[Web mapping]]\n| language         = Multilingual\n| registration     = Yes\n| owner            = [[Google]]\n| launch_date      = {{start date and age|2008|6|23}}\n| current_status   = Defunct {{end date and age|2017|3|31}}\n| revenue          =\n}}\n\n'''Google Map Maker''' was a map editing service launched by [[Google]] in June 2008.<ref>{{cite web |title = Making your mark on the world |first1 = Lalitesh |last1 = Katragadda |first2 = Sanjay |last2 = Jain |url = https://maps.googleblog.com/2008/06/making-your-mark-on-world.html |website = Google Maps blog |publisher = [[Google]] |date = 23 June 2008 |accessdate = 16 January 2017 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160313173331/https://maps.googleblog.com/2008/06/making-your-mark-on-world.html |archivedate = 13 March 2016}}</ref> In geographies where it is hard to find providers of good map data, user contributions were used to increase map quality. Changes to Google Map Maker were intended to appear on [[Google Maps]] only after sufficient review by Google moderators. Google Map Maker was used at Google [[Mapathon]] events held annually.\n\nIn November 2016, Google announced that Google Map Maker would be retired and merged with Google Maps.<ref name=\"lumb\">{{cite web |title = Google will retire Map Maker, the tool that let anyone update Maps |first = David |last = Lumb |url = https://www.engadget.com/2016/11/09/google-will-retire-map-maker-the-tool-that-let-anyone-update-ma/ |website = [[Engadget]] |date = 9 November 2016 |accessdate = 16 January 2017 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20161115035749/https://www.engadget.com/2016/11/09/google-will-retire-map-maker-the-tool-that-let-anyone-update-ma/ |archivedate = 15 November 2016 |url-status = live }}</ref> Google Map Maker was officially shut down on March 31, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Map Maker update [February 2017]|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!topic/map-maker/5m7xLsiEFB0|publisher=Google Product Forums|accessdate=2 March 2017|date=24 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Interface==\nUsing the find or browse tools, contributors were able to add and draw features directly onto a map where the borders had already been drawn, and could add features such as [[road]]s, [[railway]]s, [[river]]s and so on. In addition, users could add specific buildings and services onto the map such as local [[business]]es and services.<ref name=\"lumb\" />\n\nThree kinds of drawing tools were available: placemark (a single point of interest on the map), line (for drawing roads, railways, rivers, and the like) and [[polygon]] (for defining boundaries and borders, adding parks, lakes and other large features). The approach encouraged by users and by Google was to trace features such as roads from the existing satellite imagery. This approach was not useful in areas with poor satellite imagery, and users consequently created less map data in those areas.\n\nNew users' contributions were moderated by more experienced users or reviewers at Google to ensure quality and prevent [[vandalism]]. As users made more successful contributions, their edits were less closely monitored and may have been published on the map straight away. Certain larger features may have taken a long time to appear on the map as they were waiting to be rendered by the server.\n\nContributors could assign areas of the map as their 'neighbourhood', that is an area they know well enough to make detailed contributions to. Users could also moderate the contributions of others within their neighbourhood. This information was private; the neighbourhood a user selected was not publicly associated with the users' account.<ref name=pulse>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/mapmaker/pulse |title=Google Map Maker |publisher=Google.com |date= |accessdate=11 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Availability==\nAs of 6 March 2016, the service was available in [[Bangladesh]], [[Belarus]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Brazil]], [[Cambodia]], [[Canada]], [[Costa Rica]], [[Croatia]], [[Czech Republic]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], [[Denmark]] (not including [[Greenland]] and the [[Faroe Islands]]), [[Egypt]], [[El Salvador]], [[Estonia]], [[France]], [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]], [[Germany]], [[Hungary]], [[India]], [[Iran]], [[Iraq]], [[Italy]], [[Kazakhstan]], [[Kuwait]], [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]], [[Malaysia]], [[Mexico]], [[Moldova]], [[Morocco]], [[Nepal]], the [[Netherlands]], [[New Zealand]], [[Nigeria]], [[Pakistan]], [[Panama]], [[Peru]], the [[Philippines]], [[Poland]], [[Puerto Rico]], [[Romania]], [[Russia]], [[Serbia]], [[Slovakia]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Sweden]], [[Taiwan]], [[Ukraine]], the [[United Kingdom]], the [[United States]], [[Venezuela]], and [[Vietnam]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Countries being mapped|url=https://support.google.com/mapmaker/answer/155415?hl=en|website=Map Maker Help|accessdate=24 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n==2015 vandalism incident==\nIn April 2015, Google removed user-created Map Maker content that showed an \"[[Android (operating system)|Android]] robot urinating on the [[Apple Inc.#Logo|Apple logo]]\" and a separate feature saying \"Google review policy is crap\", after they were discovered on [[Google Maps]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hern|first1=Alex|title=Google Maps hides an image of the Android robot urinating on Apple|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2015/apr/24/google-maps-hides-an-image-of-the-android-robot-pissing-on-apple|accessdate=10 May 2015|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=24 April 2015}}</ref> Following the \"large scale prank\", Google disabled auto-approval and user moderation, and on 8 May, the Map Maker team announced that editing would be temporarily disabled worldwide as of 12 May 2015.<ref name=\"BBC News 12 May 2015\">{{cite web | title= Google suspends Map Maker because of vandalism|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-32704566 |date= 12 May 2015 | website= BBC News | accessdate= 12 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kanakarajan|first1=Pavithra|title=Map Maker will be temporarily unavailable for editing starting May 12, 2015|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!category-topic/map-maker/news-and-announcements/crFEbGXJ-HI|accessdate=10 May 2015|publisher=Google Product Forums|date=8 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nGoogle reenabled the service in six countries in August 2015, with plans to enable in other countries in the following weeks.<ref name=\"6country\">{{cite web|last1=Kanakarajan|first1=Pavithra|title=Map Maker will be enabled in six countries starting today|url=https://productforums.google.com/forum/#!topic/map-maker/JeAFzDcTFfQ|website=Google Product Forums|publisher=Alphabet Inc.|accessdate=16 August 2015}}</ref> On 10 August, editing was re-opened to Bangladesh, Brazil, Canada, India, the Philippines, and Ukraine; Google relied on regional moderators to review edits as an extra precaution, in addition to automated and human moderation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://searchengineland.com/google-map-maker-back-up-in-six-countries-more-to-follow-227473 |title=Google Map Maker Back Up In Six Countries With More To Follow Soon |last=Sterling |first=Greg |work=[[Search Engine Land]] |date=10 August 2015 |accessdate=10 August 2015}}</ref> On 26 August, Google Map Maker re-opened to 45 more countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2490133,00.asp |title=Google Map Maker Back in Action in U.S. |author=Moscaritolo, Angela |work=[[PC Magazine]] |date=August 26, 2015 |accessdate=August 26, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Criticism==\nMap Maker required contributors to grant Google a \"... perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide, royalty-free, and non-exclusive license to reproduce, adapt, modify, translate, publish, publicly perform, publicly display, distribute, and create derivative works of the User Submission\".<ref>[http://www.google.com/mapmaker/mapfiles/s/terms_mapmaker.html Terms of Service for Google Map Maker]</ref> While Google provided a form to request Map Maker data downloads,<ref>{{cite web|title=Map Maker Data Download|url=https://services.google.com/fb/forms/mapmakerdatadownload/|publisher=Google|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> it provided no programmatic access to data. There were expressions of concern that Google was taking advantage of open communities,<ref>{{cite web|last=Maron|first=Mikel|title=We Need to Stop Google's Exploitation of Open Communities |url=http://brainoff.com/weblog/2011/04/11/1635|publisher=Brainoff|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> and large contributors to Map Maker, such as the [[World Bank]]'s project partnering with Google, were viewed critically.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fitzpatrick|first=Alex|title=Google Maps & World Bank Join Forces, So Why Isn\u2019t Everyone Smiling?|url=http://mashable.com/2012/01/19/google-maps-world-bank/|publisher=Mashable|accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Heller|first=Nathaniel|title=Why We're Worried about Google's Deal with the World Bank |url=http://www.globalintegrity.org/blog/google-world-bank-map-deal|publisher=Global Integrity|accessdate=23 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Yandex Map Editor]]\n* [[Mapping Bangladesh]]\n* [[Here Map Creator]]\n* [[OpenStreetMap]]\n* [[Wikimapia]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/https://mapmaker.google.com/mapmaker Google Map Maker website]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/*/sites.google.com/site/mapmakerpedia/ Google Map Makerpedia]\n\n{{Google Maps navbox}}\n{{Google Inc.}}\n{{OpenStreetMap}}\n\n[[Category:Crowdsourcing]]\n[[Category:Google Maps|Maker]]\n[[Category:Google services|Map Maker]]\n[[Category:Web Map Services]]\n[[Category:2008 software]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Internet properties disestablished in 2017]]\n[[Category:Discontinued Google software|Map Maker]]\n", "name_user": "72.89.54.8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Map_Maker"}
{"title_page": "Hirzel Canning Company & Farms", "text_new": "\n\n\n[[File:Hirzel_Canning_Company.jpg|right|frameless|269x269px]]\n\n= Hirzel Canning Company =\n{{Sidebar||content4=Northwood, Ohio, United States|heading4=Headquarters|heading8=Website|content7=Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes - Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut - Star Cross|heading7=Brands|content6=Canned Tomatoes, Tomato Juice, Tomato and Pasta Sauces, Salsa, and Sauerkraut|heading6=Products|content5=Steve Hirzel, CEO|heading5=Key People|style=|name=Hirzel Canning Company|content3=Carl R. Hirzel|heading3=Founder|content2=1923; 97 years|heading2=Founded|content1=Food Processing|heading1=Industry|image=|title=Hirzel Canning Company|pretitle=|content8=[http://www.deifratelli.com www.deifratelli.com]}}\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company is a food products corporation founded in 1923 by Carl R. Hirzel.  The company focuses on Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes and Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut. Hirzel Canning Company is continually ran by Hirzel family members with the 4th generation currently in leadership roles within the company.</big>\n\n\n== <big>History</big> ==\n<big>Carl R. Hirzel was a brewmaster who switched to growing and canning vegetables during the onset of [[Prohibition]]. He traveled from Switzerland to New York with his wife, Lena to become brewers in the United States. He later moved near [[Toledo, Ohio]] to be closer to his brothers.  Upon seeing the quality of soil the area had to offer, Carl purchased Hirzel Farms and began growing and selling cabbage in 1920.  A plentiful cabbage harvest in 1923 convinced Carl to begin producing [[sauerkraut]], a process very similar to beer making.  He started selling his sauerkraut under the name Star Cross.  Star Cross Sauerkraut became so popular among local shop owners that just one year later the Hirzel family was receiving requests to grow [[Tomato|tomatoes]].  In 1924, Hirzel Farms harvested their first tomatoes.</big> <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ohiogrocers.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Canning-Spotlight.pdf|title=Canning Spotlight|last=|first=|date=September 2018|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/|title=Our Family {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/buckeye-built/buckeye-built-dei-fratelli-keeps-roots-planted-in-ohio-selling-canned-tomatoes-products-across-us|title=Buckeye Built: Dei Fratelli keeps roots planted in Ohio, selling canned tomato products across US|date=2019-11-15|website=WEWS|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Star_Cross_Delivery.jpg|left|300x300px]]\n<big>With the success of the tomatoes and sauerkraut, Hirzel Canning Company was incorporated in 1947 with Karl A. Hirzel, son of Carl R. Hirzel, as president and his wife Rosalie as secretary.  Hirzel Canning Company has stayed close to their roots being headquartered in [[Northwood, Ohio]] on the same property where the original Hirzel Family home stands. Since their incorporation, Hirzel Canning Company has thrived and has underwent multiple expansions throughout the years. In 1954, the [[Pemberville, Ohio]] plant was purchased and in 1982 the company expanded again to a third plant in [[Ottawa, Ohio]].  These expansions have allowed Hirzel Canning Company to produce more product while staying true to their original purpose:</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/posts/dei-fratelli-brand-tomatoes_deifratelli-foodproduction-foodmanufacturing-activity-6655132778960613376-qMmU|title=Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes posted on LinkedIn|website=www.linkedin.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n<br />\n=== <big>'''\"Hirzel Canning Company feeds people. Through quality food, innovation, stewardship of resources and resourcefulness, this family conviction endures.\"'''</big> ===\n<br />\n\n== <big>Charitable Reach</big> ==\n[[File:Feed_The_Children.jpg|thumb|Hirzel Canning Company providing tomatoes during a Feed the Children event  in 2019]]\n<big>From the very beginning, Carl R. Hirzel would put a few cans of tomatoes and sauerkraut aside to give to each grocer personally and say, \"Make sure to give this to your wife.\"  Hirzel Canning Company keeps this community spirit alive by being supportive and involved in the community that has been so supportive of them.</big> <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n<br />\n\n=== <big>Local Involvement  (Northwood, Ohio)</big> ===\n\n* <big>SeaGate Food Bank</big>\n** <big>\"Stuff-the-Truck\" and \"Pack-a-Pickup\" have provided food to many local families in need  during the holiday seasons.  Hirzel Canning Company matches all donations for this event pound for pound.</big><ref name=\":2\" />\n* <big>Walleyes for Wounded Warriors</big> \n** <big>This weekend long fishing trip serves to bring together veterans and first-responders that were injured in the line of duty.  Hirzel Canning Company is proud to continually provide the kickoff meal for this event.</big><ref name=\":2\" />\n* <big>Mobile Meals of Toledo</big> \n** <big>Hirzel Canning Company helps to sponsor the annual Chili Cook Off.  All proceeds from this event help to fund the Mobile Meals of Toledo's Delivered Meal Program.</big> <ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/community-involvement/|title=Community Involvement {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company continually supports other local charities including Cherry St. Mission Ministries, [[Habitat for Humanity]], and Little Sisters of the Poor.</big> <ref name=\":2\" />\n[[File:FTC_3.jpg|left|thumb|267x267px|Hirzel Canning Company continues to support their community through their Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes ]]\n\n=== <big>National Involvement</big> ===\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company knows that just as their support goes outside their local community, so does their duty to continue to feed people.  Hirzel Canning Company continues to support their national community as well by donating to [[Feed the Children]] and [[Feeding America|Feeding America.]]</big> <ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":0\" />\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br />\n== <big>Hirzel Canning Company Facilities</big> ==\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company currently owns and operates 3 plants, all located in Northwest Ohio.  The closeness of these plants allows for Hirzel Canning Company to carefully watch and monitor every step from planting to production.  Hirzel Canning Company is proud to have most of their tomatoes travel less than 10 miles to one of their facilities from the fields they were picked.  This allows for full packaging to be completed in a short time and for the freshest tomatoes to be available all year long.</big>  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/buckeye-built/buckeye-built-dei-fratelli-keeps-roots-planted-in-ohio-selling-canned-tomatoes-products-across-us|title=Buckeye Built: Dei Fratelli keeps roots planted in Ohio, selling canned tomato products across US|date=2019-11-15|website=WEWS|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>  <big>As the plants have expanded Hirzel Canning Company has designed its own conveyor system, taking tomatoes from the truck to the final packaging, allowing for cleaning, sorting, peeling and dicing along the way. This allows Hirzel Canning Company to show the complete process it takes to get a tomato from the farm to a grocery store shelf.</big> <ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.limaohio.com/archive/16428/news-business-home_top-50187080-seizing-the-dei|title=Seizing the \u2018Dei\u2019|date=2015-06-28|website=The Lima News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>  <ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://plantpath.osu.edu/HirzelFieldTrip|title=Field Trip to Hirzel Canning Co. and Farms {{!}} Plant Pathology|website=plantpath.osu.edu|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> <ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.foodengineeringmag.com/articles/93131-northwest-ohio-food-processing?v=preview|title=Northwest Ohio food processing|website=www.foodengineeringmag.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.freshplaza.com/article/2125839/canada-tomato-canning-plant-happy-to-call-ottawa-home/|title=Canada: Tomato canning plant happy to call Ottawa home|website=www.freshplaza.com|language=EN|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Pemberville_Final.png|thumb|Packing Tomatoes at the Pemberville, Ohio Plant ]]\n\n=== Plant Locations ===\n\n* <big>Northwood, Ohio (Headquarters)</big>\n* <big>Pemberville, Ohio  (acquired in 1954)</big>\n* <big>Ottawa, Ohio (acquired in 1982)</big> <ref name=\":3\" />\n\n=== Packaging Capabilities ===\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company caters to multiple customers including industrial, institutional, and retail.  This variety of customers allows Hirzel Canning Company to package their product in a variety of ways.  Today, Hirzel Canning Company can package their products in retail cans, foodservice cans, and industrial drums and totes.  By providing their products to many larger customers, Hirzel Canning Company utilizes reusable transport packaging to reduce costs for customers as well as improve sustainability in industrial packaging.</big>  <ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=http://ciftinnovation.org/hirzel-adds-new-products-with-help-from-cift/|title=CIFT - Partnering with Hirzel to Streamline Processes and Gain Savings|website=CIFT|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Industrial_Final.jpg|left|thumb|254x254px|Hirzel Canning Company utilizes reusable transport packaging to reduce costs and to improve sustainability]]\n\n\n\n\n\n'''<big>\u201cOne of the secrets behind a high quality product in a can or a glass jar is the high quality fruit coming in from the farm. We can\u2019t make it any better; we can only preserve how good it is coming out of the field.\u201d</big>''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ofbf.org/2009/06/22/feeling-saucy-2/|title=Feeling Saucy|date=2009-06-22|website=Ohio Farm Bureau|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n\n\n<br />\n== <big>Certifications</big> <ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/products/|title=Products {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!\n!\n|-\n|<big>'''[[The Non-GMO Project|Project Non-GMO]] Verified'''</big> <ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/dei-fratelli-achieved-non-gmo-162617367.html|title=Dei Fratelli Has Achieved Non-GMO Project Verification|website=finance.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/our-label/|title=Our Label {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n|<big>Most of Hirzel Canning Company's products are Non-GMO Project verified</big>\n|-\n|'''<big>[[Bisphenol A|BPA Free]]</big>''' <ref name=\":13\" />\n|<big>All Hirzel Canning Company's cans are BPA-Free</big>\n|-\n|'''<big>[[Gluten|Gluten Free]]</big>''' <ref name=\":13\" />\n|<big>Dei Fratelli products are not certified gluten free, however none of their product contain gluten.  With gluten in their facilities they take extra precautions through their Allergen Awareness program for gluten and other major allergens.Gluten Free</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''Level 2 [https://www.sqfi.com/why-get-certified/about-sqf-program/ SQF Food Safety Program]'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>3 Plants with Onsite Quality Control Labs</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''Allergen Control Program'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|\n|-\n|<big>'''Kosher Certified'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>Quality Kosher</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''FSMA Compliant'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>[[Hazard analysis and critical control points|HACCP]] Certified, PCQI Trained</big>\n|-\n|<big>[[Aseptic processing|'''Commercially Sterile''']]</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>High Temperature, Short Time, Particulate Integrity</big><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakeryandsnacks.com/Article/2013/08/12/Hirzel-Canning-Truly-Tomato-range-in-SIG-Combibloc-cartons|title=Dei Fratelli: Canned food business \u2018not going away\u2019|last=bakeryandsnacks.com|website=bakeryandsnacks.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\n== <big>Hirzel Farms</big> ==\n<big>The Hirzel farming operation was the first step in the process that led to preserving and canning Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes and Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut.  Today, Lou Kozma Jr,. a 4th generation Hirzel family member, is the general manager.  Hirzel Farms follows a sustainability model that is based on environmental and social responsibilities.</big>  <ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/meet-our-growers/|title=Meet Our Growers {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Farms continues to innovate by being the primary research entity for new planting methods and plant nutrition.  By continuing this research, Hirzel Farms is able to produce a stronger and more flavorful tomato through their non-GMO practices.  Researching the growing of their processing crops allows Hirzel Farms to find better ways of providing the consumer with a safe and healthy product. This research includes reduced pesticide use and planting various varieties.</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=12|title=Crop Production|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  \n\n\n<big>Hirzel Farms provides only a small amount of raw product that Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes requires, as this allows the Hirzel family to continue to innovate and grow better tomatoes, just as founder Carl R. Hirzel directed.</big> <ref name=\":4\" />\n\n=== <big>Organic Farming</big> ===\n<big>In the late 70s, Hirzel Farms began converting some of their acreage to organic production.  In 1982, 345 acres were certified for organic production and now Hirzel Farms has over 1000 acres certified under the [http://www.goa-online.org/ Global Organic Alliance]. Hirzel currently grows corn, soybeans, smelt, wheat, rye, and triticale in their organic fields.  Hirzel Farms maintains their organic fields through strict crop rotations, utilization of cover crops, and making their own [[compost]].</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=12|title=Crop Production|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== <big>Composting</big> ===\n<big>In 1992, Hirzel Farms saw an opportunity as tomato peels and cabbage trimmings left the Hirzel Canning Company's facilities.  They saw that they could take these unwanted items and use them to put back into their products as compost.  Today, Hirzel Farms operates a fully-licensed, Ohio EPA Class 2 Composting Facility. This facility has allowed Hirzel Farms to  not only generate their own organic compost but also help their community at the same time by collecting compostable materials from local residences, businesses, and municipalities.</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=16|title=Composting|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> \n\n=== <big>Research and Development</big> ===\n<big>In the spring of 1991, John E. Hirzel</big>  <big>began converting some of Hirzel Farm's organic farmland to begin testing some sustainable practice agriculture.  Today, Hirzel Farms works closely with the [[Ohio Agricultural Research and Development Center]], [https://extension.osu.edu/ Ohio State Extension], [[Agricultural Research Service|USDA Agricultural Research Service]], and various other public and private research entities.</big> <ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=10444|title=Research and Development|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== <big>Agricultural Incubator Foundation</big> ===\n<big>Hirzel Farms continues to invest heavily in their community.  In 1997, Hirzel Canning Company and Farms acquired a research facility in Northwest Ohio.  This research facility is now the [https://www.agincubator.org/ Agricultural Incubator Foundation] (AIF) and it serves as a non-profit research foundation to provide their expertise and help anyone wishing to expand their knowledge on production, processing, or preservation of food. The AIF is managed daily by a Center of Innovative Food Technology employee, Paula Ray, whom along with Rebecca Singer and Isabelle Montez work with start-up food processing companies to ensure that they meet all safety requirements before taking their product from \"hobby\" to public marketplace.</big> <ref name=\":5\" />\n\n\n\n<big>At the Agricultural Incubator Foundation, Hirzel Farms manages over 100 acres of plot trails, including The John E. Hirzel Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education Site.  This site is closely managed and cared for by Wood County Extension Educator, Alan Sundermeier and contains everything that John E. Hirzel felt strongly about.</big> <ref name=\":5\" />\n\n<br />\n== <big>References</big> ==\n<references />\n\n\n\n{{portal bar|Food}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hirzel Canning Company}}\n[[Category:Olive oil]]\n[[Category:Brand name condiments]]\n[[Category:Italian brands]]\n[[Category:Food and drink companies established in 1923]]\n[[Category:1923 establishments in Ohio]]\n", "text_old": " [[File:Hirzel_Canning_Company.jpg|right|frameless|269x269px]]\n\n= Hirzel Canning Company =\n{{Sidebar||content4=Northwood, Ohio, United States|heading4=Headquarters|heading8=Website|content7=Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes - Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut - Star Cross|heading7=Brands|content6=Canned Tomatoes, Tomato Juice, Tomato and Pasta Sauces, Salsa, and Sauerkraut|heading6=Products|content5=Steve Hirzel, CEO|heading5=Key People|style=|name=Hirzel Canning Company|content3=Carl R. Hirzel|heading3=Founder|content2=1923; 97 years|heading2=Founded|content1=Food Processing|heading1=Industry|image=|title=Hirzel Canning Company|pretitle=|content8=[http://www.deifratelli.com www.deifratelli.com]}}\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company is a food products corporation founded in 1923 by Carl R. Hirzel.  The company focuses on Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes and Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut. Hirzel Canning Company is continually ran by Hirzel family members with the 4th generation currently in leadership roles within the company.</big>\n\n\n== <big>History</big> ==\n<big>Carl R. Hirzel was a brewmaster who switched to growing and canning vegetables during the onset of [[Prohibition]]. He traveled from Switzerland to New York with his wife, Lena to become brewers in the United States. He later moved near [[Toledo, Ohio]] to be closer to his brothers.  Upon seeing the quality of soil the area had to offer, Carl purchased Hirzel Farms and began growing and selling cabbage in 1920.  A plentiful cabbage harvest in 1923 convinced Carl to begin producing [[sauerkraut]], a process very similar to beer making.  He started selling his sauerkraut under the name Star Cross.  Star Cross Sauerkraut became so popular among local shop owners that just one year later the Hirzel family was receiving requests to grow [[Tomato|tomatoes]].  In 1924, Hirzel Farms harvested their first tomatoes.</big> <ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ohiogrocers.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Canning-Spotlight.pdf|title=Canning Spotlight|last=|first=|date=September 2018|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/|title=Our Family {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/buckeye-built/buckeye-built-dei-fratelli-keeps-roots-planted-in-ohio-selling-canned-tomatoes-products-across-us|title=Buckeye Built: Dei Fratelli keeps roots planted in Ohio, selling canned tomato products across US|date=2019-11-15|website=WEWS|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Star_Cross_Delivery.jpg|left|300x300px]]\n<big>With the success of the tomatoes and sauerkraut, Hirzel Canning Company was incorporated in 1947 with Karl A. Hirzel, son of Carl R. Hirzel, as president and his wife Rosalie as secretary.  Hirzel Canning Company has stayed close to their roots being headquartered in [[Northwood, Ohio]] on the same property where the original Hirzel Family home stands. Since their incorporation, Hirzel Canning Company has thrived and has underwent multiple expansions throughout the years. In 1954, the [[Pemberville, Ohio]] plant was purchased and in 1982 the company expanded again to a third plant in [[Ottawa, Ohio]].  These expansions have allowed Hirzel Canning Company to produce more product while staying true to their original purpose:</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.linkedin.com/posts/dei-fratelli-brand-tomatoes_deifratelli-foodproduction-foodmanufacturing-activity-6655132778960613376-qMmU|title=Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes posted on LinkedIn|website=www.linkedin.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n<br />\n=== <big>'''\"Hirzel Canning Company feeds people. Through quality food, innovation, stewardship of resources and resourcefulness, this family conviction endures.\"'''</big> ===\n<br />\n\n== <big>Charitable Reach</big> ==\n[[File:Feed_The_Children.jpg|thumb|Hirzel Canning Company providing tomatoes during a Feed the Children event  in 2019]]\n<big>From the very beginning, Carl R. Hirzel would put a few cans of tomatoes and sauerkraut aside to give to each grocer personally and say, \"Make sure to give this to your wife.\"  Hirzel Canning Company keeps this community spirit alive by being supportive and involved in the community that has been so supportive of them.</big> <ref name=\":1\" />\n\n<br />\n\n=== <big>Local Involvement  (Northwood, Ohio)</big> ===\n\n* <big>SeaGate Food Bank</big>\n** <big>\"Stuff-the-Truck\" and \"Pack-a-Pickup\" have provided food to many local families in need  during the holiday seasons.  Hirzel Canning Company matches all donations for this event pound for pound.</big><ref name=\":2\" />\n* <big>Walleyes for Wounded Warriors</big> \n** <big>This weekend long fishing trip serves to bring together veterans and first-responders that were injured in the line of duty.  Hirzel Canning Company is proud to continually provide the kickoff meal for this event.</big><ref name=\":2\" />\n* <big>Mobile Meals of Toledo</big> \n** <big>Hirzel Canning Company helps to sponsor the annual Chili Cook Off.  All proceeds from this event help to fund the Mobile Meals of Toledo's Delivered Meal Program.</big> <ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/community-involvement/|title=Community Involvement {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company continually supports other local charities including Cherry St. Mission Ministries, [[Habitat for Humanity]], and Little Sisters of the Poor.</big> <ref name=\":2\" />\n[[File:FTC_3.jpg|left|thumb|267x267px|Hirzel Canning Company continues to support their community through their Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes ]]\n\n=== <big>National Involvement</big> ===\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company knows that just as their support goes outside their local community, so does their duty to continue to feed people.  Hirzel Canning Company continues to support their national community as well by donating to [[Feed the Children]] and [[Feeding America|Feeding America.]]</big> <ref name=\":2\" /><ref name=\":0\" />\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<br />\n== <big>Hirzel Canning Company Facilities</big> ==\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company currently owns and operates 3 plants, all located in Northwest Ohio.  The closeness of these plants allows for Hirzel Canning Company to carefully watch and monitor every step from planting to production.  Hirzel Canning Company is proud to have most of their tomatoes travel less than 10 miles to one of their facilities from the fields they were picked.  This allows for full packaging to be completed in a short time and for the freshest tomatoes to be available all year long.</big>  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news5cleveland.com/news/buckeye-built/buckeye-built-dei-fratelli-keeps-roots-planted-in-ohio-selling-canned-tomatoes-products-across-us|title=Buckeye Built: Dei Fratelli keeps roots planted in Ohio, selling canned tomato products across US|date=2019-11-15|website=WEWS|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>  <big>As the plants have expanded Hirzel Canning Company has designed its own conveyor system, taking tomatoes from the truck to the final packaging, allowing for cleaning, sorting, peeling and dicing along the way. This allows Hirzel Canning Company to show the complete process it takes to get a tomato from the farm to a grocery store shelf.</big> <ref name=\":7\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.limaohio.com/archive/16428/news-business-home_top-50187080-seizing-the-dei|title=Seizing the \u2018Dei\u2019|date=2015-06-28|website=The Lima News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>  <ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://plantpath.osu.edu/HirzelFieldTrip|title=Field Trip to Hirzel Canning Co. and Farms {{!}} Plant Pathology|website=plantpath.osu.edu|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> <ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.foodengineeringmag.com/articles/93131-northwest-ohio-food-processing?v=preview|title=Northwest Ohio food processing|website=www.foodengineeringmag.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.freshplaza.com/article/2125839/canada-tomato-canning-plant-happy-to-call-ottawa-home/|title=Canada: Tomato canning plant happy to call Ottawa home|website=www.freshplaza.com|language=EN|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Pemberville_Final.png|thumb|Packing Tomatoes at the Pemberville, Ohio Plant ]]\n\n=== Plant Locations ===\n\n* <big>Northwood, Ohio (Headquarters)</big>\n* <big>Pemberville, Ohio  (acquired in 1954)</big>\n* <big>Ottawa, Ohio (acquired in 1982)</big> <ref name=\":3\" />\n\n=== Packaging Capabilities ===\n<big>Hirzel Canning Company caters to multiple customers including industrial, institutional, and retail.  This variety of customers allows Hirzel Canning Company to package their product in a variety of ways.  Today, Hirzel Canning Company can package their products in retail cans, foodservice cans, and industrial drums and totes.  By providing their products to many larger customers, Hirzel Canning Company utilizes reusable transport packaging to reduce costs for customers as well as improve sustainability in industrial packaging.</big>  <ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=http://ciftinnovation.org/hirzel-adds-new-products-with-help-from-cift/|title=CIFT - Partnering with Hirzel to Streamline Processes and Gain Savings|website=CIFT|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n[[File:Industrial_Final.jpg|left|thumb|254x254px|Hirzel Canning Company utilizes reusable transport packaging to reduce costs and to improve sustainability]]\n\n\n\n\n\n'''<big>\u201cOne of the secrets behind a high quality product in a can or a glass jar is the high quality fruit coming in from the farm. We can\u2019t make it any better; we can only preserve how good it is coming out of the field.\u201d</big>''' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ofbf.org/2009/06/22/feeling-saucy-2/|title=Feeling Saucy|date=2009-06-22|website=Ohio Farm Bureau|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n\n\n\n<br />\n== <big>Certifications</big> <ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/products/|title=Products {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref> ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!\n!\n|-\n|<big>'''[[The Non-GMO Project|Project Non-GMO]] Verified'''</big> <ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web|url=http://finance.yahoo.com/news/dei-fratelli-achieved-non-gmo-162617367.html|title=Dei Fratelli Has Achieved Non-GMO Project Verification|website=finance.yahoo.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref><ref name=\":13\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/our-label/|title=Our Label {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n|<big>Most of Hirzel Canning Company's products are Non-GMO Project verified</big>\n|-\n|'''<big>[[Bisphenol A|BPA Free]]</big>''' <ref name=\":13\" />\n|<big>All Hirzel Canning Company's cans are BPA-Free</big>\n|-\n|'''<big>[[Gluten|Gluten Free]]</big>''' <ref name=\":13\" />\n|<big>Dei Fratelli products are not certified gluten free, however none of their product contain gluten.  With gluten in their facilities they take extra precautions through their Allergen Awareness program for gluten and other major allergens.Gluten Free</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''Level 2 [https://www.sqfi.com/why-get-certified/about-sqf-program/ SQF Food Safety Program]'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>3 Plants with Onsite Quality Control Labs</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''Allergen Control Program'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|\n|-\n|<big>'''Kosher Certified'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>Quality Kosher</big>\n|-\n|<big>'''FSMA Compliant'''</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>[[Hazard analysis and critical control points|HACCP]] Certified, PCQI Trained</big>\n|-\n|<big>[[Aseptic processing|'''Commercially Sterile''']]</big> <ref name=\":11\" />\n|<big>High Temperature, Short Time, Particulate Integrity</big><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakeryandsnacks.com/Article/2013/08/12/Hirzel-Canning-Truly-Tomato-range-in-SIG-Combibloc-cartons|title=Dei Fratelli: Canned food business \u2018not going away\u2019|last=bakeryandsnacks.com|website=bakeryandsnacks.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-21}}</ref>\n|}\n\n\n== <big>Hirzel Farms</big> ==\n<big>The Hirzel farming operation was the first step in the process that led to preserving and canning Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes and Silver Fleece Brand Sauerkraut.  Today, Lou Kozma Jr,. a 4th generation Hirzel family member, is the general manager.  Hirzel Farms follows a sustainability model that is based on environmental and social responsibilities.</big>  <ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.deifratelli.com/about-our-family/meet-our-growers/|title=Meet Our Growers {{!}} Dei Fratelli Tomatoes|website=www.deifratelli.com|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n\n<big>Hirzel Farms continues to innovate by being the primary research entity for new planting methods and plant nutrition.  By continuing this research, Hirzel Farms is able to produce a stronger and more flavorful tomato through their non-GMO practices.  Researching the growing of their processing crops allows Hirzel Farms to find better ways of providing the consumer with a safe and healthy product. This research includes reduced pesticide use and planting various varieties.</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=12|title=Crop Production|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>  \n\n\n<big>Hirzel Farms provides only a small amount of raw product that Dei Fratelli Brand Tomatoes requires, as this allows the Hirzel family to continue to innovate and grow better tomatoes, just as founder Carl R. Hirzel directed.</big> <ref name=\":4\" />\n\n=== <big>Organic Farming</big> ===\n<big>In the late 70s, Hirzel Farms began converting some of their acreage to organic production.  In 1982, 345 acres were certified for organic production and now Hirzel Farms has over 1000 acres certified under the [http://www.goa-online.org/ Global Organic Alliance]. Hirzel currently grows corn, soybeans, smelt, wheat, rye, and triticale in their organic fields.  Hirzel Farms maintains their organic fields through strict crop rotations, utilization of cover crops, and making their own [[compost]].</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=12|title=Crop Production|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== <big>Composting</big> ===\n<big>In 1992, Hirzel Farms saw an opportunity as tomato peels and cabbage trimmings left the Hirzel Canning Company's facilities.  They saw that they could take these unwanted items and use them to put back into their products as compost.  Today, Hirzel Farms operates a fully-licensed, Ohio EPA Class 2 Composting Facility. This facility has allowed Hirzel Farms to  not only generate their own organic compost but also help their community at the same time by collecting compostable materials from local residences, businesses, and municipalities.</big> <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=16|title=Composting|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref> \n\n=== <big>Research and Development</big> ===\n<big>In the spring of 1991, John E. Hirzel</big>  <big>began converting some of Hirzel Farm's organic farmland to begin testing some sustainable practice agriculture.  Today, Hirzel Farms works closely with the [[Ohio Agricultural Research and Development Center]], [https://extension.osu.edu/ Ohio State Extension], [[Agricultural Research Service|USDA Agricultural Research Service]], and various other public and private research entities.</big> <ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hirzelfarms.com/?page_id=10444|title=Research and Development|website=Hirzel Farms|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n=== <big>Agricultural Incubator Foundation</big> ===\n<big>Hirzel Farms continues to invest heavily in their community.  In 1997, Hirzel Canning Company and Farms acquired a research facility in Northwest Ohio.  This research facility is now the [https://www.agincubator.org/ Agricultural Incubator Foundation] (AIF) and it serves as a non-profit research foundation to provide their expertise and help anyone wishing to expand their knowledge on production, processing, or preservation of food. The AIF is managed daily by a Center of Innovative Food Technology employee, Paula Ray, whom along with Rebecca Singer and Isabelle Montez work with start-up food processing companies to ensure that they meet all safety requirements before taking their product from \"hobby\" to public marketplace.</big> <ref name=\":5\" />\n\n\n\n<big>At the Agricultural Incubator Foundation, Hirzel Farms manages over 100 acres of plot trails, including The John E. Hirzel Sustainable Agriculture Research and Education Site.  This site is closely managed and cared for by Wood County Extension Educator, Alan Sundermeier and contains everything that John E. Hirzel felt strongly about.</big> <ref name=\":5\" />\n\n<br />\n== <big>References</big> ==\n<references />\n\n\n\n{{portal bar|Food}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hirzel Canning Company}}\n[[Category:Olive oil]]\n[[Category:Brand name condiments]]\n[[Category:Italian brands]]\n[[Category:Food and drink companies established in 1923]]\n[[Category:1923 establishments in Ohio]]\n", "name_user": "DeiFratelliTomatoes", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hirzel_Canning_Company_%26_Farms"}
{"title_page": "Try Again (Aaliyah song)", "text_new": "{{short description|2000 single by Aaliyah}}\n{{other uses|Try Again (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Try Again\n| cover      = Aaliyah-Try-Again-cover.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Aaliyah]] featuring [[Timbaland]]\n| album      = [[Romeo Must Die (soundtrack)|Romeo Must Die: The Album]] {{noitalic|and}} [[Aaliyah (album)|Aaliyah {{noitalic|(international version)}}]]\n| released   = February 22, 2000\n| format     = {{hlist|[[CD single|CD]]|[[Twelve-inch single|12\"]]}}\n| recorded   = Fall 1999\n| studio     = [[Manhattan Center]]<br />{{small|([[New York City, New York]])}}\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]<ref>{{cite web|last=Whaley|first=Natelege|date=August 17, 2012|url=http://theboombox.com/randb-songs-hip-hop/|title=The Hip-Hop Effect: 20 R&B Songs Sampling Rap Beats and Lyrics|publisher=The Boombox. [[AOL]]|accessdate=December 28, 2013}}</ref>|[[Electronic dance music|EDM]]<ref name=\"complex.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/the-best-aaliyah-songs/try-again|title=The 25 Best Aaliyah Songs7. \"Try Again\" f/ Timbaland (2000)|website=Complex}}</ref>|[[Hip hop music|hip hop]]<ref name=\"complex.com\"/>|[[Electro (music)|electro]]<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2011/12/the-top-100-best-songs-of-the-2000s/aaliyah-try-again|title=The 100 Best Songs of the 2000s|website=Complex}}</ref>|[[dance-pop]]<ref name=\"ReferenceA\"/>}}\n| length     = 4:49\n| label      = {{hlist|[[Blackground Records|Blackground]]|[[Virgin Records|Virgin]]}}\n| writer     = {{flatlist|\n*[[Static Major|Stephen Garrett]]\n*[[Timbaland|Timothy Mosley]]\n}}\n| producer   = [[Timbaland]]\n| chronology = [[Aaliyah]]\n| prev_title = [[I Don't Wanna (Aaliyah song)|I Don't Wanna]]\n| prev_year  = 1999\n| next_title = [[Come Back in One Piece]]\n| next_year  = 2000\n}}\n\n\"'''Try Again'''\" is a song by American singer [[Aaliyah]]. It was written by [[Static Major]] and [[Timbaland|Timothy Mosley]], and produced by [[Timbaland]]. The song was released on February 22, 2000, as the lead single for [[Romeo Must Die (soundtrack)|the soundtrack]] to the film ''[[Romeo Must Die]]'', and was later included on international pressings of the singer's [[Aaliyah (album)|self-titled album]]. \"Try Again\" features an intro in which Timbaland pays homage to [[Eric B. & Rakim]] by rapping the duo's opening verse from \"[[I Know You Got Soul (Eric B. & Rakim song)|I Know You Got Soul]]\".\n\n==Background==\nIn 1999, Aaliyah landed her first movie role in ''[[Romeo Must Die]]'', released March 22, 2000. A loose adaptation of [[William Shakespeare]]'s ''[[Romeo and Juliet]]'', Aaliyah starred opposite martial artist [[Jet Li]], playing a couple who fall in love amid their warring families. It grossed US$18.6 million in its first weekend, ranking number two at the box office.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,85088,00.html|title='Romeo' and Julia |last=Wolk|first=Josh|date=March 26, 2000|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|publisher=[[Time Inc.|Time]]|accessdate=May 10, 2009}}</ref> In addition to acting, Aaliyah served as an executive producer of the [[Romeo Must Die (soundtrack)|film soundtrack]], to which she contributed four songs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/08/27/arts/aaliyah-22-singer-who-first-hit-the-charts-at-14.html|title=Aaliyah, 22, Singer Who First Hit the Charts at 14|last=Pareles|first=Jon|date=August 27, 2001|work=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|accessdate=May 10, 2009}}</ref> Aaliyah revealed that the production team \"actually talked about the soundtrack before we even shot the movie\".<ref>{{Cite book|last = Farley|first = Christopher John|authorlink = |title = Aaliyah: More Than a Woman|publisher = Simon and Schuster|year = 2001|isbn = 978-1-4165-5215-4 |page=106 |ref = harv}}</ref> On February 18, 2000, it was announced that \"Try Again\" would be released as the lead single of ''[[Romeo Must Die#Soundtrack|Romeo Must Die: The Album]]'' (2000), while an accompanying music video would be directed by [[Wayne Isham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1424656/aaliyah-dmx-ginuwine-pitch-romeo-lp.jhtml|title=Aaliyah, DMX, Ginuwine Pitch In For \"Romeo\" LP|last=Basham|first=David|date=February 18, 2000|accessdate=August 25, 2011|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]}}</ref> It was physically released on February 22, 2000.<ref name=ultratop/> \"Try Again\" was recorded at Sound on Sound Studios in New York and it was originally written as an inspirational song.\n<ref name=TryAgain>{{cite web |url=http://www.waxpoetics.com/blog/features/articles/look-back-20-years-on-the-short-but-influential-career-of-aaliyah/2/|title=A look back 20 years to the debut album of Aaliyah, the R. Kelly scandal, and her Timbaland-produced follow-up that set the R&B format on fire|accessdate=August 2, 2018|work=[[Wax Poetics]]}}</ref>  According to engineer Jimmy Douglass it was \"written to inspire young people, but Barry [Hankerson] heard it and told them, \u2018It\u2019s got to be about love.\"\n<ref name=TryAgain/>  After all of the changes that was made to the song, the melody and hook were the same but the lyrics were about love.\n<ref name=TryAgain/>\n\n==Composition==\n{{listen|filename=Aaliyah - Try Again.ogg|title=\"Try Again\"\n|description=A 24-second sample of the song's chorus, which features Aaliyah singing over an [[electro music|electro]]-inspired background.\n|pos= left\n|format=[[Ogg]]}}\n\n\"Try Again\" is a song written by [[Static Major|Stephen Garrett]] and [[Timbaland|Timothy Mosley]], and produced by [[Timbaland]].<ref name=sheet>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdVPE.asp?ppn=MN0035322|title=Aaliyah Try Again \u2013 Digital Sheet Music|work=Music Notes|publisher=[[Universal Music Publishing Group]]|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref> Timbaland's fuzzy, booming soundscape is influenced by [[acid house]]. [[Yahoo! Music]] formally known as \"Launch\" mentioned that the song's sound is associated with [[Detroit techno]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.launch.yahoo.com/l_reviews_s/14561.html|title=LAUNCH, Music on Yahoo! - Aaliyah - 'Try Again'|date=22 January 2005|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050122130149/http://uk.launch.yahoo.com/l_reviews_s/14561.html|archivedate=22 January 2005}}</ref> Aaliyah's sinuous singing comprises simple vocal riffs, which are repeated and refracted to echo the manipulated [[Loop (music)|loops]] that produce the song's digital rhythm. The chorus line, \"If at first you don't succeed, then dust yourself off and try again\", is hypnotically repeated in a fashion similar to the [[sampling (music)|sampling]] and vocal manipulation found in [[house music]].<ref name=\"Sanneh\">{{cite news|last=Sanneh|first=Kelefa|date=September 2, 2001|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2001/09/02/arts/a-pioneer-briefly-of-a-new-sound.html|title=A Pioneer, Briefly, Of a New Sound|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=December 9, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108045550/http://www.nytimes.com/2001/09/02/arts/a-pioneer-briefly-of-a-new-sound.html|archivedate=November 8, 2012|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Music Notes, the song is composed in the [[Key (music)|key]] of [[C-sharp minor|C{{music|sharp}} minor]] and is set in [[time signature]] of [[common time]] with a [[tempo]] of 92 [[beats per minute]], while Aaliyah's vocal range spans from G{{music|sharp}}<sub>3</sub> to G{{music|sharp}}<sub>4</sub>.<ref name=sheet/> In the song's intro, Timbaland pays homage to [[Eric B. & Rakim]] by rapping the duo's opening verse from \"[[I Know You Got Soul (Eric B. & Rakim song)|I Know You Got Soul]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/aaliyahs-top-10-billboard-hits-227937|title=Aaliyah's Top 10 Billboard Hits|date=August 25, 2011|accessdate=March 21, 2019|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nChuch Taylor from ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' felt that Aaliyah had another smash hit on her hands and he praised her vocal styling saying \"Aaliyah's sultry vocals slide all over the futuristic beat\". When it came to the production of the song he had a mixed response to it, although he thought the synth sample and snare alternate lived up to expectations for the song he ultimately felt that the synth sample becomes grating as the song progresses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nA4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA26&dq=aaliyah+try+again+review&pg=PA26#v=onepage&q=aaliyah+try+again+review&f=false|title=Billboard|first=Nielsen Business Media|last=Inc|date=18 March 2000|publisher=Nielsen Business Media, Inc.|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n\"Try Again\" debuted on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] on the week of March 18, 2000 at number fifty-eight,<ref name=billboardhistory>{{cite web|url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=aaliyah|chart=all}}|title=Try Again - Aaliyah|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref> reaching number one on the week of June 17, 2000.<ref name=billboardhistory/> It also peaked at number one on the [[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Hot 100 Airplay]] chart, number three on the [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Mainstream Top 40]] chart and number four on the [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|Hot R&B Singles & Tracks]] chart.<ref name=billboardhistory/> On the Year-End chart for 2000, the song reached number twelve.<ref name=\"billboardci\"/>\n\nIn the United Kingdom, \"Try Again\" debuted and peaked at number five on the [[UK Singles Chart]] on July 16, 2000\u2015for the week ending July 22, 2000<ref name=chartstats>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/The%20Game|title=The Official Charts Company \u2013 Aaliyah \u2013 Try Again|publisher=[[Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref>\u2015while staying in the top seventy-five of the chart for twelve weeks. The song has sold over 209,000 copies and it is Aaliyah's best selling single in that region.<ref name=chartstats/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/more-than-a-woman-aaliyah-remembered-on-her-birthday__16126/|title=\nMore Than A Woman: Aaliyah remembered on her birthday|accessdate=2018-01-16|work=[[Official Charts]]}}</ref>\n\n\"Try Again\" also achieved commercial success elsewhere in Europe, peaking within the top five on the charts in Belgium, Netherlands, Norway, and Switzerland.<ref name=ultratop>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/en/showitem.asp?interpret=Aaliyah&titel=Try+Again&cat=s|title=Aaliyag - Try Again (song)|year=2000|accessdate=August 25, 2011|publisher=Hung Medien}}</ref> \nIn Germany, the song peaked at number five on the [[Media Control Charts|German Singles Chart]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/title/Aaliyah/Try+Again/single|title=Die ganze Musik im Internet: Charts, News, Neuerscheinungen, Tickets, Genres, Genresuche, Genrelexikon, K\u00fcnstler-Suche, Musik-Suche, Track-Suche, Ticket-Suche - musicline.de|language=German|publisher=[[Media Control Charts]]. PhonoNet GmbH|accessdate=August 18, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121003192151/http://musicline.de/de/chartverfolgung_summary/title/Aaliyah/Try+Again/single|archive-date=October 3, 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIn Australia, the song reached number eight on the [[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]].<ref name=\"pandora.nla.gov.au\">{{cite web |url=http://www.aria.com.au/issue566.PDF |title=Pandora Archive |publisher=Pandora.nla.gov.au |date=2006-08-23 |accessdate=2011-01-19 |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=http://pandora.nla.gov.au/pan/23790/20020221-0000/www.aria.com.au/issue566.PDF |archivedate=2002-02-21 }}</ref> It became the country's fifty-first best-selling song of 2000.<ref name=\"ARIA 2000 Year-End Chart\"/>\n\n==Music video==\n===Synopsis===\nThe music video was directed by [[Wayne Isham]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1424656/aaliyah-dmx-ginuwine-pitch-in-for-romeo-lp/|title=Aaliyah, Dmx, Ginuwne Pitch In For \"Romeo\" LP|date=February 18, 2000|publisher=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> and It begins with [[Jet Li]] entering a hall of mirrors and Aaliyah stepping in, wearing a revealing low-cut bra and tight low-rise leather pants, [[Timbaland]] is also shown. The room is dim with a shallow pool and circle light in the center to resemble the moon shining over the ocean represented by said pool. \n\n===Reception===\nThe music video for \"Try Again\" made its official television debut on [[MTV]] during the week of March 5, 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nA4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA81&vq=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&lr&rview=1&pg=PA81#v=snippet&q=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=March 18, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> On the week of March 12, 2000 the video debuted on the cable network channel [[VH1]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sg4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA7&lr&rview=1&pg=PA79#v=onepage&q=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=March 25, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> Meanwhile on the week of March 19, 2000 the video debuted on [[The Box (U.S. TV channel)|The Box]], the following month later during the week of April 3, 2000 the video debuted on the [[BET]] network channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ww4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA102&vq=aaliyah%20try%20again&lr&rview=1&pg=PA102#v=snippet&q=aaliyah%20try%20again&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=April 1, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4w4EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA101&vq=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&lr&rview=1&pg=PA101#v=snippet&q=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=April 15, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> During its chart run the music video for \"Try Again\" received heavy TV airplay on multiple music video count down shows. For the week ending on May 8, 2000 the video was the number one most played video on BET.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PA8EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA109&vq=aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&lr&rview=1&pg=PA109#v=snippet&q=aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=May 20, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>  On MTV the video was the third most played video on the network during the week ending on May 22, 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mQ8EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA107&vq=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&lr&rview=1&pg=PA107#v=snippet&q=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20mtv&f=false|title=Video Monitor|date=June 3, 2000|work=[[Billboard Magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Legacy==\n{{Quote box\n |quote = \"Try Again\" helped smuggle the innovative techniques of [[electronic dance music]] onto the American pop charts, and it established Aaliyah as pop music's most futuristic star.\n |source = \u2014 [[Kelefa Sanneh]], ''[[The New York Times]]''<ref name=\"Sanneh\"/>\n |quoted = true\n |bgcolor = #FFFFF0\n |salign = center\n |align = right\n |width = 25%\n |border = 1px\n |fontsize = 90%\n}}\n\"Try Again\" was the first song ever to reach number one on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] based solely on the strength of its radio airplay.<ref name=column>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mw8EAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA103&ots=PrtqOiZqJW&dq=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20first%20song%20to%20go%20number%201%20off%20of%20airplay%20billboard&pg=PA103#v=onepage&q=Aaliyah%20try%20again%20first%20song%20to%20go%20number%201%20off%20of%20airplay%20billboard&f=false|title=Hot 100 Spotlight |last=Pietroluongo|first=Silvio|date=June 17, 2000|accessdate=March 21, 2019|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> \"Try Again\" was nominated for a [[Grammy Award for Best Female R&B Vocal Performance]] at the [[43rd Grammy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1435904/43rd-annual-grammy-award-nominees/|title=43rd Annual Grammy Award Nominees|date=January 3, 2001|accessdate=March 21, 2019|work=[[MTV News]]}}</ref>  while its music video won two [[MTV Video Music Awards]] for [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Female Video|Best Female Video]] and [[MTV Video Music Award for Best Video from a Film|Best Video from a Film]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1433642/chili-peppers-tape-show-live-dvd-video.jhtml|title=Chili Peppers To Tape Show For Live DVD, Video|last=Basham|first=David|date=September 21, 2000|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref> The song was also nominated on the seventh annual [[Soul Train Music Awards|Soul Train Lady of Soul Awards]] in the category of Song of the Year; however, Aaliyah lost to gospel artist [[Yolanda Adams]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1448482/aaliyah-missed-at-lady-soul-awards.jhtml|title=Aaliyah's Absence Felt At Lady Of Soul Awards|date=August 29, 2001|last=vanHorn|first=Teri|work=[[MTV]]|publisher=[[MTV Networks]]|accessdate=August 25, 2011}}</ref>\n\n\"Try Again\" was featured on ''Billboard''{{'}}s Hot 100 Songs of the Decade list at number ninety-eight,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/#/charts-decade-end/hot-100-songs?year=2009&begin=91&order=position|title=Hot 100 Songs of the Decade|accessdate=August 25, 2011|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]]}}</ref> while appearing at number eighty-six on the ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' list of the 100 Best Songs of the Decade.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/news/story/31248926/100_best_songs_of_the_decade/4|title=100 Best Songs of the Decade|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|publisher=[[Jann Wenner]]}}</ref> The song was also ranked at number 18 on Rolling Stone's 20 Biggest Songs of the Summer: The 2000s list.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/20-biggest-songs-of-the-summer-the-2000s-11671/18-aaliyah-try-again-221593/|title=20 Biggest Songs of the Summer: The 2000s\n|date=July 30, 2014|work=[[Rolling Stone Magazine|Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=July 29, 2018}}</ref> On January 31, 2005, ''[[Pitchfork Media]]'' ranked the song number thirty-seven on its list of the Top 100 Singles of 2000-04.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/staff-lists/5949-the-top-100-singles-of-2000-04-part-one/7/|title=Pitchfork: Staff Lists: The Top 100 Singles of 2000-04|date=January 31, 2005|author=Pitchfork Staff|accessdate=August 25, 2011|publisher=[[Pitchfork Media]]}}</ref> ''[[Complex Magazine]]'' ranked the single 43rd on its list of the 100 Best Songs of the 2000s, while it finished 60th on [[Slant Magazine]]'s Best of the Aughts: Singles list.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2011/12/the-top-100-best-songs-of-the-2000s/aaliyah-try-again|title= The 100 Best Songs of the 2000s|work=[[Complex Magazine]]|publisher=[[Complex Magazine]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/feature/best-of-the-aughts-singles/214/page_5|title= Best of the Aughts: Singles|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|publisher=[[Slant Staff]]}}</ref> In September 2011, [[VH1]] included \"Try Again\" in their list of 100 Greatest Songs of the 2000s, placing it at number 65.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stereogum.com/826992/vh1-100-greatest-songs-of-the-00s/top-stories/lead-story/|title=VH1 100 Greatest Songs Of The \u201900s|date=29 September 2011|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[The Village Voice]]''{{'}}s [[Pazz & Jop]] annual year-end critics' poll ranked \"Try Again\" at number 10 to find the best music of 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/xg/pnj/pjres00.php|title=Pazz & Jop Critics' Poll, 2000|publisher=robertchristgau.com}}</ref> British publication [[The Daily Telegraph]] ranked try again at number 42 on their 100 songs that defined the Noughties list.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/rockandpopfeatures/6198897/100-songs-that-defined-the-Noughties.html|title=100 songs that defined the Noughties|first=Neil|last=McCormick|date=18 September 2009|publisher=|via=www.telegraph.co.uk}}</ref> [[Yahoo]] included \"Try Again\" on their 15 Chart toppers that didn't suck (2000's edition) list <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/music/15-chart-toppers-didn-t-154743000.html|title=15 Chart Toppers that Didn\u2019t Suck (2000s Edition)|publisher=}}</ref> In March 2020 ''Billboard'' ranked the song at number 14 on their \"The 100 Greatest Songs of 2000\" list.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/list/9339652/best-songs-of-2000-top-100|title=The 100 Greatest Songs of 2000: Staff Picks|date=March 23, 2020|publisher=[[Billboard magazine|Billboard]]|accessdate=March 25, 2020}}</ref> [[George Michael]] sampled \"Try Again\" in his 2002 hit song \"[[Freeek!]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/house/article/the-15-best-george-michael-songs|title=The 15 Best George Michael Songs - The House Next Door - Slant Magazine|publisher=}}</ref> German [[Neue Deutsche H\u00e4rte|NDH]] band [[Knorkator]] covered the song in their album ''[[Ich hasse Musik]]''. In 2013 Dr. Danny from ''[[The Mindy Project]]'' taught the choreography of the video to Mindy in an episode of the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/celebrity/the-mindy-project-chris-messina-dances-to-aaliyah-try-again/|title=VIDEO: The Mindy Project's Chris Messina Busts a Move to Aaliyah|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2013/12/04/chris-messina-dancing-to-aaliyah-mindy-project/|title=Watch Chris Messina dancing to Aaliyah on 'The Mindy Project'|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n==Track listings==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n*'''CD single'''<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Try Again|others=Aaliyah|date=2000|type=CD single liner notes|publisher=Blackground Entertainment|id=VUSCDF167, 7243 8 96835 2 3}}</ref>\n# \"Try Again\" [radio edit] \u2013 4:04\n# \"Try Again\" [Timbaland Remix] \u2013 4:59\n# \"Try Again\" [D'Jam Hassan Remix] \u2013 5:28\n# \"Try Again\" [Instrumental] \u2013 4:43\n{{col-2}}\n*'''12\" vinyl'''<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title=Try Again|others=Aaliyah|date=2000|type=Vinyl liner notes|publisher=Hostile Records|id=7243 8968356 1}}</ref>\n# \"Try Again\" [radio edit] \u2013 4:04 \t\n# \"Try Again\" [Instrumental] \u2013 4:43 \t\n# \"Try Again\" [Timbaland Remix] \u2013 4:59\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2000)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|8|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|19|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|6|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|5|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadadance|2|chartid=7213|accessdate=November 27, 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Canadatopsingles|5|chartid=7187|accessdate=November 27, 2018}}\n|-\n|Denmark ([[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry|IFPI]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/00s/2000/MM-2000-07-29.pdf|title=Top National Sellers|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=17|issue=31|page=9|date=July 29, 2000|accessdate=November 2, 2019}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mBAEAAAAMBAJ&lpg=PA74&dq=Aaliyah%20eurochart%20try%20again&pg=PA75#v=onepage&q=Aaliyah%20eurochart%20try%20again&f=false|title=Hits of the World|work=Billboard|accessdate=December 23, 2017}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|6\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Europe ([[Music & Media|European Radio Top 50]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/00s/2000/MM-2000-08-19.pdf|title=European Radio Top 50|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=17|issue=34|page=32|date=August 19, 2000|access-date=February 8, 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|17\n|-\n{{singlechart|France|26|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|5|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|songid=4311|accessdate=October 9, 2018}}\n|-\n|Iceland ([[\u00cdslenski listinn|\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40]])<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://timarit.is/files/12883840.pdf#navpanes=1&view=FitH|title=\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40 (Vikuna 19.8. - 26.8. 2000 33. Vika)|publisher=Dagbla\u00f0i\u00f0 V\u00edsir|accessdate=July 15, 2018|language=is}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\t\n|-\n{{singlechart|Ireland3|34|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=December 10, 2015}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Italy|19|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Dutch40|3|year=2000|week=25|accessdate=December 8, 2017}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|3|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|13|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Norway|5|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n|Portugal ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Fonogr\u00e1fica Portuguesa|AFP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/00s/2000/MM-2000-09-09.pdf|title=Top National Sellers|work=Music & Media|page=9|date=September 9, 2000|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|5\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|26|date=2000-09-10}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Sweden|15|artist=Aaliyah|song=Try Again|accessdate=August 18, 2011}}\n|-\n{{s